Bejide, the wife of a former Deputy Governor of Ondo State, Ali Olanusi is dead. It was gathered that the deceased died at the age of 77 on Tuesday in Akure following a brief illness. Olanusi, a chieftain of the All Progressives Congress, was the deputy to the former Governor Olusegun Mimiko between 2009 and 2015. Kidnapped Kaduna Catholic Priest Regains Freedom CJN Hits Back At AGF Over Utterances Against Judiciary She died ahead of her husband’s planned birthday celebration. The Ondo State chapter of the APC has however commiserated with the Olanusi’s family in a statement issued by the state Publicity Secretary of the party, Alex Kalejaiye. The statement read, “The state chairman of the party, Engr. Ade Adetimehin, described sad development as ill-timed, shocking and unfortunate. He said Alhaja was a strong pillar behind the husband’s political success story. “The party chairman urged Baba Olanusi, the bereaved families, and entire Supare community in Akoko South West Local Government to take solace in that the departed lived a worthy and fulfilled life.”